-- India Monsoon Rains 21% Below Normal Since June 1, Bureau Says
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2012-07-16T14:04:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/india-monsoon-rains-21-below-normal-since-june-1-bureau-says.html
India’s monsoon, which accounts for
more than 70 percent of annual rainfall, was 21 percent below a
50-year average since June 1, the nation’s weather bureau said
today.  The nation got 243.1 millimeters of rainfall in the June 1
to July 16 period, the  India Meteorological Department  said on
its website. That is less than the 308.2 millimeter average
considered normal for the period, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
